## What is MeetAndRead?

MeetAndRead is a compact, always-on-top desktop widget that records and transcribes audio in real time using [Whisper](https://github.com/ggerganov/whisper.cpp) (via `pywhispercpp`). It captures microphone input and Windows system audio (WASAPI loopback), transcribes speech live, and produces formatted Markdown transcripts with speaker identification.

The widget sits on your desktop like a record button вҖ” click to start, click to stop. A live closed-captioning overlay shows what's being said as it happens. When you stop recording, a stronger model runs post-processing for higher accuracy, and the final transcript is saved to disk.

<p align="center">
  <img src="docs/assets/screenshot-widget.png" alt="MeetAndRead Widget" width="400">
</p>

---

## Features

### рҹҺҷпёҸ Audio Capture
- **Microphone input** вҖ” capture your voice via any recording device
- **System audio** вҖ” WASAPI loopback captures what others are saying (Windows 11)
- **Dual-source** вҖ” record both simultaneously for complete coverage

### рҹ“қ Real-Time Transcription
- **Live closed captions** вҖ” CC-style overlay shows speech as it happens
- **Whisper models** вҖ” choose tiny, base, or small for real-time; base through large for post-processing
- **Confidence coloring** вҖ” low-confidence words highlighted so you can spot gaps
- **Phrase detection** вҖ” 3-second silence detection for natural turn-taking

### рҹ”Ҡ Speaker Identification
- **Voice signatures** вҖ” automatic speaker embedding and matching via sherpa-onnx
- **Speaker diarization** вҖ” identify who said what in multi-person conversations
- **Persistent signatures** вҖ” recognized speakers remembered across recordings

### рҹҺӣпёҸ Polished Desktop Widget
- **Aetheric Glass design** вҖ” translucent, always-on-top floating widget
- **Drag & dock** вҖ” move anywhere on screen, snaps to desktop edges
- **System tray** вҖ” minimize to tray, runs quietly in the background
- **Audio source lobes** вҖ” toggle mic and system audio with overlapping buttons

### вҡҷпёҸ Settings & Management
- **Model selection** вҖ” choose real-time and post-process models independently
- **Benchmark history** вҖ” see WER and speed for each model on your hardware
- **Recording management** вҖ” browse, review, and delete past recordings
- **Transcript scrub** вҖ” re-transcribe with a stronger model and compare results

### рҹҸ—пёҸ Production Ready
- **Portable build** вҖ” PyInstaller onedir, no Python needed to run
- **CI/CD** вҖ” automated testing and GitHub Releases on tag push
- **Resource monitoring** вҖ” live CPU/RAM tracking with threshold warnings

---

## Install

### Pre-built Release (Recommended)

Download the latest zip from [GitHub Releases](https://github.com/NachoTek/meetandread/releases):

1. Download `meetandread-v0.6.0.zip`
2. Extract anywhere
3. Run `meetandread.exe`

No Python installation required.

### From Source

```bash
# Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/NachoTek/meetandread.git
cd meetandread

# Install with dev dependencies
pip install -e ".[dev]"

# Run
python -m meetandread.main
```

**Requirements:** Python 3.10+, Windows 11

---

## Quick Start

1. **Launch** MeetAndRead вҖ” the widget appears on your desktop
2. **Select audio sources** вҖ” click the mic and/or system audio lobes around the record button
3. **Click the record button** вҖ” recording starts, live transcription appears in the CC overlay
4. **Click again to stop** вҖ” post-processing runs with a stronger model
5. **Review** вҖ” open the Settings panel вҶ’ History tab to browse transcripts

Your recordings and transcripts are saved in your Documents folder under `MeetAndRead/`.

---

## How It Works

MeetAndRead uses a **hybrid transcription** architecture:

```
в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ     в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ     в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
в”Ӯ Audio Input  в”Ӯв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–¶в”Ӯ Real-Time Engine в”Ӯв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–¶в”Ӯ CC Overlay      в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ (mic+system) в”Ӯ     в”Ӯ (tiny/base Whisper)в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ (live display)  в”Ӯ
в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ     в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ     в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ
                            в”Ӯ
                     audio saved to disk
                            в”Ӯ
                            в–ј
                    в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ     в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
                    в”Ӯ Post-Processing  в”Ӯв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–¶в”Ӯ Markdown        в”Ӯ
                    в”Ӯ (base/small/med) в”Ӯ     в”Ӯ Transcript      в”Ӯ
                    в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ     в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ
                            в”Ӯ
                            в–ј
                    в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
                    в”Ӯ Speaker           в”Ӯ
                    в”Ӯ Diarization       в”Ӯ
                    в”Ӯ (sherpa-onnx)     в”Ӯ
                    в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ
```

1. **Real-time** вҖ” A smaller Whisper model transcribes audio as it's captured, updating the CC overlay every ~2 seconds with accumulated context
2. **Post-processing** вҖ” When recording stops, a stronger model re-transcribes the full audio for higher accuracy
3. **Speaker diarization** вҖ” sherpa-onnx segments the audio by speaker and matches against stored voice signatures

---

## Configuration

Settings are managed through the Settings panel (click the gear lobe on the widget) and persisted in `AppData/meetandread/settings.json`.

| Setting | Default | Description |
|---------|---------|-------------|
| Real-time model | `tiny` | Whisper model for live transcription |
| Post-process model | `base` | Whisper model for final transcript |
| Enable post-processing | `true` | Run stronger model after recording |
| Speaker diarization | `true` | Identify speakers in recordings |
| Confidence threshold | `0.7` | Below this, words are highlighted |

---

## Project Structure

```
src/meetandread/
в”ңв”Җв”Җ main.py                      # Application entry point
в”ңв”Җв”Җ audio/
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ capture/                 # Audio source backends (WASAPI, sounddevice)
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ storage/                 # PCM buffering, WAV finalization
в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ session.py               # Recording session coordinator
в”ңв”Җв”Җ config/                      # Settings models and persistence
в”ңв”Җв”Җ hardware/                    # Hardware detection and model recommendations
в”ңв”Җв”Җ performance/                 # Resource monitoring, WER benchmarking
в”ңв”Җв”Җ recording/                   # Recording controller (UI-facing API)
в”ңв”Җв”Җ speaker/                     # Speaker diarization and voice signatures
в”ңв”Җв”Җ transcription/               # Whisper engine, streaming pipeline, transcript store
в””в”Җв”Җ widgets/                     # PyQt6 UI (widget, panels, theme, tray icon)
```

